data.text: Draghi: The Governing Council welcomes the ongoing discussions on completing the banking union and the capital markets union, and on further deepening Economic and Monetary Union
Draghi: Regarding fiscal policies, the increasingly solid and broad-based expansion strengthens the case for rebuilding fiscal buffers, especially in countries where government debt remains high
Draghi: Recent volatility in the exchange rate represents a source of uncertainty which requires monitoring with regard to its possible implications for the medium-term outlook for price stability
Draghi: Domestic price pressures remain muted overall and have yet to show convincing signs of a sustained upward trend
Draghi: The strong cyclical momentum and the ongoing reduction of economic slack strengthen our confidence that inflation will converge towards our inflation aim of below, but close to, 2%
Draghi: Incoming information confirms a robust pace of economic expansion, which accelerated more than expected in the second half of 2017

Draghi: If outlook becomes less favourable or if financial conditions become inconsistent with progress towards sustained adjustment in path of inflation, we stand ready to increase the asset purchase programme in size and/or duration
Draghi: Net asset purchases, at the new monthly pace of €30 billion, are intended to run until the end of September 2018, or beyond, if necessary
Draghi: We continue to expect interest rates to remain at their present levels for an extended period of time, and well past the horizon of our net asset purchases
